During a visit to Fort Bragg, North Carolina, President Joe Biden expressed his gratitude to the military and their families. He shared a personal anecdote about his wife, Jill Biden, and their Valentine's Day tradition. He also praised the military as the finest in the world and expressed his pride in being their Commander-in-Chief. The President thanked the troops for their service and acknowledged the sacrifices made by their families. He closed by jokingly mentioning his wife's instruction to return to her side and introducing the chaplain to say a prayer before dinner.